    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-06-15T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-06-15T12:00:00-05:00" n="356"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d356">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 658.119/446</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_MIN1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morris</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stockholm</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-06-15T18:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 15, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received June 16, 7.13 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2309. When the Foreign Minister handed me the note referred to in my 2308, June
                    15, 5 p.m., he also gave me the following note which I send herewith without
                    comment: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>One of the letters which were exchanged by the delegates, letter No. 7 of
                            Mr. <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_HFL1">Leverton
                                Harris</persName> to Mr. <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_CG1"
                                >Carlsson</persName>,<note n="1" xml:id="d356fn1">
                                <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_1269">p.
                                1269</ref>.</note> contains in regard to clause 3 the following
                            passage: “It is understood, etc.” Although I have been told that Mr.
                                <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_CG1">Carlsson</persName>
                            suggested this passage, I feel it my duty in order to avoid all
                            misunderstanding to make expressly this reserve, that the Swedish
                            Government in adhering to the arrangement did not intend in any way to
                            recognize the right of the Associated Governments to make such a
                            requisition. I will be grateful if you will kindly bring the statement
                            to the knowledge of the Associated Governments.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>A similar note at the same time was handed to the British, French, and Italian
                    Ministers to be sent to their respective Governments.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_MIN1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Morris</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
